339	Brigham Young	Brigham Young (/ˈbrɪɡəm/; June 1, 1801 – August 29, 1877) was an American leader in the Latter Day Saint movement and a settler of the Western United States. He was the President of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints (LDS Church) from 1847 until his death in 1877. He founded Salt Lake City and he served as the first governor of the Utah Territory. Young also led the foundings of the precursors to the University of Utah and Brigham Young University.\nYoung had a variety of nicknames, among the most popular being "American Moses" (alternatively, the "Modern Moses" or the "Mormon Moses"), because, like the biblical figure, Young led his followers, the Mormon pioneers, in an exodus through a desert, to what they saw as a promised land. Young was dubbed by his followers the "Lion of the Lord" for his bold personality, and was also commonly called "Brother Brigham" by Latter-day Saints. Young was a polygamist and was involved in controversies regarding black people and the Priesthood, the Utah War, and the Mountain Meadows massacre.	\N	\N	\N	http://cdn1.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/images/brigham-young-1.jpg	\N	Wikipedia.org	http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brigham_Young	["http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/18/USVA_headstone_emb-11.svg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/6/62/PD-icon.svg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/6/69/P_vip.svg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/7/7e/Brigham_Young_statue_at_BYU.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/8b/This_Is_The_Place_Heritage_Park.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/c/c2/Brigham_Young_and_company_1870.PNG", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/fa/Wikiquote-logo.svg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/20/Brigham_Young_by_Charles_William_Carter.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/8f/Brigham_Young_and_his_brothers.jpg", "http:/