73	Francis Drake	Sir Francis Drake, vice admiral (c. 1540 – 27 January 1596) was an English sea captain, privateer, navigator, slaver, and politician of the Elizabethan era. Drake carried out the second circumnavigation of the world, from 1577 to 1580.\nElizabeth I of England awarded Drake a knighthood in 1581. He was second-in-command of the English fleet against the Spanish Armada in 1588. He died of dysentery in January 1596 after unsuccessfully attacking San Juan, Puerto Rico.\nHis exploits were legendary, making him a hero to the English but a pirate to the Spaniards to whom he was known as El Draque. King Philip II was said to have offered a reward of 20,000 ducats, about £4 million (US$6.5M) by modern standards, for his life.\n\n	\N	\N	\N	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/9a/Sir_Francis_Drake_And_His_Coat_Of_Arms.gif	\N	Wikipedia.org	http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Francis_Drake	["http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/9a/Sir_Francis_Drake_And_His_Coat_Of_Arms.gif", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/4c/Wikisource-logo.svg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f5/Francis_Drake_Signature.svg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2b/Drake_CA_1590.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/45/Loutherbourg-Spanish_Armada.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7d/Gheeraerts_Francis_Drake_1591.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/97/New_Albion._English_galleon_%22Golden_Hinde%22_by_Sir_Francis_Drake._Oil_on_canvas._60_x_90_cm..jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/00/NPG_Drake.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/47/Pirate_Flag_of_Jack_Rackham.svg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/fc/Padlock-silver.svg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7d/Sfec_goldenhind02crop.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/57/Sfdrake42.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/4/4a/Commons-logo.s