371	Fauvism	Fauvism is the style of les Fauves (French for "the wild beasts"), a loose group of early twentieth-century Modern artists whose works emphasized painterly qualities and strong color over the representational or realistic values retained by Impressionism. While Fauvism as a style began around 1900 and continued beyond 1910, the movement as such lasted only a few years, 1904–1908, and had three exhibitions. The leaders of the movement were Henri Matisse and André Derain.	\N	\N	\N	http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_Yg3lYRZvzTo/TP-zqZhVfMI/AAAAAAAAA-0/EdNnX3kiiuQ/s1600/maurice-de-vlaminck-restaurant.jpg	\N	Wikipedia.org	http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fauvism	["http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/fb/Matisse-Woman-with-a-Hat.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/2/21/SeineChatou.JPG", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/c/c4/Self-portrait_in_studio_by_Andr%C3%A9_Derain.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/2/2d/Matisse_-_Green_Line.jpeg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/5/59/Matisse-Open-Window.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/5/58/La_Petite_Lima.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/8/83/Dongen-Hat.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/8/8f/Henri_Matisse_Self-Portrait_in_a_Striped_T-shirt_%281906%29.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/b/b5/Matisse_Souvenir_de_Biskra.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/0/07/Matisse-Luxe.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/0/05/Derain_CharingCrossBridge.png", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/b/be/Jean_Metzinger%2C_1907%2C_Paysage_color%C3%A9_aux_oiseaux_aquatique%2C_oil_on_canvas%2C_74_x_99_cm%2C_Mus%C3%A9e_d%E2%80%99Art_Moderne_de_la_Ville_de_Paris.jpg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/4c/Wikisource-logo.svg", "http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/